## Writing Rules
- Follow the section structure from the plan.
- ALL content in {{ language }}, formal academic register.
- Headings must be plain text with `#` markers only — do NOT wrap headings in `**bold**` or `*italic*`.
{% if language and 'Greek' in language %}
- For **Greek** section headings, use sentence-style capitalisation (see *Greek — titles and `#` headings* above), not English Title Case — correct the plan’s headings if they look like the latter.
{% endif %}
- Use `[[source_id]]` citation markers: `Σύμφωνα με [[smith2020]], ...`
- Page references: `[[source_id|σ. 45]]`
- Multiple sources: `[[smith2020]] [[jones2019]]` — separate markers, NEVER combined.
- Do NOT write a References/Βιβλιογραφία section — the export step generates it.
- Do NOT write literal `(Author, Year)` citations.
- When data is best presented in tabular form (comparisons, statistics, timelines), use standard markdown tables:
  ```
  | Header 1 | Header 2 |
  |----------|----------|
  | Cell 1   | Cell 2   |
  ```
- Use tables only when they genuinely improve clarity — do NOT overuse them.
